<p><a href="#link2.1">▲</a><strong>red_green</strong></p>

<p><em>Short name: </em>red_green</p>

<p><em>Original file name suffix</em>: […]_Red_[…]_Green_color</p>

<p><em>Processing description</em>: Pseudocolor image that combines the color images of both sides of the given page. The reverse side is aligned with the front side and the two color images are blended together, emphasizing the red separation of the front and the green separation of the reverse side.</p>

<p><em>Aspects of manuscript enhanced</em>: Blotting and bleed through, red stains</p>

<p class="space2"><a id="link35" name="link35"></a><em>Lead Scientist</em>: Knox</p>

<p><a href="#link2.1">▲</a><strong>RIRL*</strong></p>

<p><em>Short name: </em>RIRL</p>

<p><em>Processing description</em>: Left and right raking infrared images are differenced and linearly contrast stretched.</p>

<p><em>Aspect of manuscript enhanced</em>: Topography</p>

<p class="space2"><a id="link36" name="link36"></a><em>Lead Scientist</em>: Knox</p>

<p><a href="#link2.1">▲</a><strong>sharpie**</strong></p>

<p><em>Short name: </em>sharpie</p>

<p><em>Original file name suffix</em>: sharpie_0505-0780</p>

<p><em>Processing description</em>: 505 nm and 780 nm wavelengths are combined in a no-veil pseudocolor image with the 780 in the red separation and the 505 in the blue and green separations. The sharpie image is made by linearly stretching the difference of the red and blue separations of the pseudocolor image.</p>

<p><em>Aspects of manuscript enhanced</em>: Primary handwritten texts, handwritten additions, miscellaneous singular stains</p>

<p class="space2"><a id="link37" name="link37"></a><em>Lead Scientist</em>: Knox</p>

<p><a href="#link2.1">▲</a><strong>sharpieratio_0505-0780*</strong></p>

<p><em>Short name: </em>sharpieratio</p>

<p><em>Processing description</em>: 505 nm and 780 nm wavelengths are divided by the 940 nm wavelength and then combined in a standard pseudocolor image. The sharpie image is made by linearly stretching the difference of the red and blue separations of the pseudocolor image.</p>

<p><em>Aspects of manuscript enhanced</em>: Primary handwritten undertexts</p>

<p><em>Lead Scientist</em>: Knox</p>

