        'value' => '<p>[View the <a href="/islandora/search/liv_000005?access=all&amp;limit=catalogue" target="_blank">critical edition</a> or download a <a href="/sites/default/files/in-his-own-words/field-diary-v-overview/liv_000005_reading_copy.zip">basic reading copy</a> of Field Diary V.]</p>

<p>In Field Diary V, Livingstone journeys from the shores of Lake Nyassa west through mountains in modern-day Malawi. Along the way, he finds plentiful food, most of it given to them by local populations. Perhaps as a result, in this diary Livingstone records far fewer instances of mutiny or struggles for authority among his men.</p>

<p class="space1" style="line-height:110%"><a href="/sites/default/files/in-his-own-words/field-diary-v-overview/liv_014087_0001-article6.jpg"><img alt="Alphabetical Adventures of Livingstone in Africa for Boys and Girls (Iredale 1941:[1]), detail. Copyright National Library of Scotland. Creative Commons Share-alike 2.5 UK: Scotland (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/scotland/)." class="media-image attr__typeof__foaf:Image img__fid__306 img__view_mode__media_original attr__format__media_original" data-popupalt-original-title="null" src="/sites/default/files/in-his-own-words/field-diary-v-overview/liv_014087_0001-article6.jpg" title="Alphabetical Adventures of Livingstone in Africa for Boys and Girls (Iredale 1941:[1]), detail. Copyright National Library of Scotland. Creative Commons Share-alike 2.5 UK: Scotland (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/scotland/)." typeof="foaf:Image&quot;" width="716" /></a><br />
