			<td colspan="2" style="line-height: 110%; padding-top: 0"><span style="font-size:12px;">(Left; top in mobile) A color image of a page of the <em>Letter from Bambarre</em> (Livingstone 1871c:[3]). <em>Copyright Peter and Nejma Beard. <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/3.0/" target="_blank">Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 3.0 Unported</a></em>. (Right; bottom) A processed spectral image of a page of the <em>Letter from Bambarre</em> (Livingstone 1871c:[3] pseudo_v3). <em>Copyright Peter and Nejma Beard. <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/3.0/" target="_blank">Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 3.0 Unported</a></em>. Ink bleedthrough in the color image, especially along the edges of the page, renders Livingstone\'s writing difficult to read. The processed image addresses this issue by using different colors to distiguish the text on the recto of the page and that that has bled through from the verso.</span></td>
