<p>The components transported by the team to Edinburgh included:</p>

<p style="margin-left: 25px">1) monochrome MegaVision E6 39 megapixel camera back (7216 X 5412 pixels; 16-bit data with approximately 12 bits of dynamic range) mounted in a technical view camera with a 60mm UV-VIS-IR lens and a color filter wheel installed for UV fluorescence studies.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 25px">2) light-emitting diode (LED) illumination panels which were placed on tripods on either side of the copy stand in symmetric downward-looking positions angled approximately 45º on either side. The team also used diffusers to create uniform and nondirectional light fields. Raking illumination was provided in two spectral bands from either side of the manuscript.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 25px">3) modified desktop computer that controlled the imaging system using MegaVision’s PhotoShoot™ 4.0 software. This software orchestrated the operation of both camera and lighting through FireWire and USB connections, respectively.</p>

