<p>The wavelengths, or colors, of the raw images included one ultraviolet, two blue, three green, two red, and five infrared wavelengths. In addition, four images were taken with raking light, i.e., light shining on the surface of the paper at such a low grazing angle that the variations in the surface are emphasized. These four images were taken from the left and right sides of the paper, in both blue and infrared light. The captured images include the following spectra and illuminations:</p>

<p style="text-align:center;"><span style="display:inline-block; text-align:left"><strong>Band = Wavelength in nanometers</strong><br />
