<p>LEAP: The <em>Livingstone Online</em> Enrichment and Access Project is a four-year initiative (2013-17) to develop <em>Livingstone Online</em> and create a critical edition of Livingstone\'s final diaries and journals (1866-73). The present history focuses on the first year and a half of LEAP (September 2013-June 2015), when the project team completed a significant portion of the work related to the redevelopment and expansion of the original <em>Livingstone Online</em> site (2005-12). The project\'s goals are detailed below. The critical edition of the diaries and journals will appear in a discrete site section when complete in 2017.</p>

<p class="space1" style="line-height:110%"><a href="/sites/default/files/about-this-site/leap-2013-2017-project-history-part-i/liv_013543_0001-crop-article.jpg"><img alt="Members of the LEAP team and collaborators view Livingstone manuscripts at the David Livingstone Centre, 2013. Copyright Michael B. Toth. Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 3.0 Unported (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/3.0/)." class="media-image attr__typeof__foaf:Image img__fid__306 img__view_mode__media_original attr__format__media_original" data-popupalt-original-title="null" src="/sites/default/files/about-this-site/leap-2013-2017-project-history-part-i/liv_013543_0001-crop-article.jpg" title="Members of the LEAP team and collaborators view Livingstone manuscripts at the David Livingstone Centre, 2013. Copyright Michael B. Toth. Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 3.0 Unported (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/3.0/)." typeof="foaf:Image&quot;" width="716" /></a><br />
<span style="font-size:12px;">Members of the LEAP team and collaborators view Livingstone manuscripts at the David Livingstone Centre, 2013. <em>Copyright Michael B. Toth. <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/3.0/" target="_blank">Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 3.0 Unported </a></em></span></p>

<p>The present narrative discusses each strand of LEAP and includes supporting documentation in the form of photographs and downloadable project documents. Collectively, these materials provide an intimate look into the development of the present site. It is our hope that the materials will serve as a resource for others interested in developing similar digital projects. The provision of these materials also grows out of our project\'s commitment to methodological transparency. In this spirit, the narrative closes with a summary of some of our principal project challenges and the lessons learned from those challenges.</p>

