<p><a href="#TOP" title="Go to table of contents" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">▲</a> <strong>Miscellaneous singular stains</strong>. Beyond the brown and red stains, the 1870 Field Diary also includes a handful of singular stains. Three such stains are present on page 1871a:LXXVI [v.1] to the left and right of page center. Two of the stains clearly lie below the writing (and have no impact on it), are about the size or a quarter or silver dollar, circular (though the one at left has a series of jagged, star-like edges and so appears to have splattered on the page), and are either light brown (left stain) or faint orange (right stain) in natural light.</p>

