			<td colspan="2" style="line-height: 110%; padding-top: 0"><span style="font-size:12px;">(Left; top in mobile) An image of a page of Field Diary X (Livingstone 1867c:[142]). (Right; bottom) An image of a page of Field Diary I (Livingstone 1865:[104]). <em>Copyright David Livingstone Centre. <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/3.0/" target="_blank">Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 3.0 Unported</a></em>. On the page in brown ink, Livingstone records local cultural and geographical information, much of it collected from African informants. The page in blue and black ink documents payments made to some of Livingstone\'s African porters.</span></td>
